New Records: Namibia scored 21 runs, the highest total in a Super Over in a men's T20 World Cup competition.
Key Match Events: David Wiese slammed 13 in the Super Over and took a wicket, defending 21 runs.
Bilal Khan bowled Michael van Lingen for a duck off the very second ball of the innings.
Mehran Khan's excellent 18th over yielded just four byes and claimed JJ Smit's wicket.
David Wiese's six in the nineteenth over helped bring the equation to five off the last over.
Mehran increased his wicket total from one to three in the first three balls of the last over by bowling Frylinck and trapping Zane Green lbw.
David Wiese hit a six and four against Bilal Khan in the Super Over.
Ruben Trumpelmann took three wickets inside the powerplay and finished with figures of 4-21.
David Wiese bagged three scalps, conceding 28 runs in 3.4 overs.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Oman failed to knock a single boundary in 44 deliveries between the 10th and 17th overs.
